name: src/index.js
propertyUtils
description:
Creates some functions that are useful when trying to decorate objects with hidden properties or getters,
or lazy loading properties, etc.  I use this a lot inside of constructor functions for singleton type objects.

params.name: target
params.description: This is the object you intend to be decorating

return.description: Returns an object with some wrapper functions around Object.defineProperty

name: hideProperties
description:
Create a bunch of hidden or non-enumerable properties on an object.
Equivalent to calling Object.defineProperty with enumerable set to false.

params.name: target
params.description: The target object which will receive the properties

name: hideGetter
description: Create a hidden getter property on the object.

params.name: target
params.description: The target object to define the hidden getter

params.name: fn
params.description: A function to call to return the desired value

params.name: options.scope
params.description: The scope / binding for the function will be called in, defaults to target

params.name: options.args
params.description: arguments that will be passed to the function

name: promiseHash
description: Treats all values of an object as Promises and resolves them.

params.name: obj
params.description: The object which has the promises to be resolved

return.description: A Promise which will resolve with the object values

name: execSync
description: Run nodes child_promise exec synchronously and capture the output, trimming any newlines or leading spaces

params.name: cmd
params.description: The command string, exactly the same as child_process.execSync

params.name: options
params.description: =             {} Any arguments for execSync will work here

name: lazy
description: Creates a lazy loading property on an object.

params.name: target
params.description: The target object to receive the lazy loader

params.name: fn
params.description: The function that will be memoized

params.name: enumerable
params.description: =             false Whether to make the property enumerable when it is loaded

name: src/query.js
query
description:
Query an array using a parameters hash which allows for different operators,
and which can easily be serialized and sent over the wire
